HEADWORD: Buhlwork
<hw>Buhl"work</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From A. Ch. <ets>Boule</ets>, a
French carver in wood.]</ety> <def>Decorative woodwork in which tortoise
shell, yellow metal, white metal, etc., are inlaid, forming scrolls,
cartouches, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>boule</asp>,
<asp>boulework</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buhlbuhl</ent>⟦br⟧
